Explanation
Consider the first word of the text (and the space which follows it) "With ". From the encoding dictionary 'W', 'i', 't', 'h' and ' ' correspond to '100100','00011','00111','111111','01001' respectively. So, the encoded version of the text begins with: 100100000110011111111101001.
